history.text: hello
Hey how's it going today
Jaws! What a classic Speilberg thriller!
you ever watched Jaws? That messed me up as a kid! lol
I was afraid to take a bath for a month. Great movie!
Were you a kid in 1975 when it originally came out to theaters?
No, it was VHS days. I wonder it they will be remaking it.

It was important for my chilhood as well. 
Robert Shaw as Quint was the most memorable character for me!
Yes, his performance was excellent, I agree.

Did you know the movie was based on a 
book by peter benchly? I never read it though
It was based on a book by Peter Benchley, I wonder what gave him the idea.
maybe he was an oceanographer like Hooper played by that one guy
I haven't read it either. Maybe one day to see if its as good as the film
You might be right, or maybe just a boring day fishing and he dreamed it all up
If it's about a giant Great White shark attacking residents of Amity island it's probably alright.
Yes, I agree!
The film is well regarded. It has a scoref or over 97% on the rotten tomatos website
Spielberg had so many great movies,  i see it's 87 on metcritics as well
When Hooper finds the giant tooth at the sunken boat and drops it, what a tense scene!
One of my favorite memories indeed
Did you know that Amity island is actually a fictional place. Can't really go there and be eaten by a big shark, unfortunately!
HAHAHA that's a shame!  Jaws was a early anamatronic so there goes that at well.
Quint offered his services for $10,000..........That was a fortune in 1975
Well, the mayor did want to keep the beaches open, after all.
Yea, not much visitors coming to the beach if the ocean is a killing ground.
They hunted the shark in a boat called the Orca, but I think they should have had a bigger boat.
They should've called the coast guard or at least david hasslehoff
The part where they sink harpons tied to bareels into the flesh of the shark used to bum me out, but not anymore. I'm glad it's dead.
Jaws is too gruesome for kids the reviewer said... Yet parents couldn't wait to show it to us lol
How strange. At least one critic characterized it as funny in a woody allen way
seeya
have a nice one

uid1response.feedback: Great movie, the other person seemed to be familiar as well.
